The paper deals with the problem of routing and rebalancing a fleet of self-driving vehicles providing on-demand mobility within a capacitated road network. This problem involves the coordination of multiple agents (vehicles) and the optimization of a complex system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also deals with the analysis and control of the system, which involves the use of network models and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the modeling of a transportation system, which involves the use of mathematical models and algorithms. Therefore, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely sub-categories.
